<paragraph id="8BED0424FFD31755FF3A09113E0EFDAA" blockId="86.[151,1437,474,1254]" box="[199,1060,582,607]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
Etymology. The name is a noun in apposition, derived from the 
<typeStatus id="54E9BA86FFD31755FC6E091039E9FDAB" box="[915,963,583,607]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFD31755FF3A093D3E05FD1A" blockId="86.[151,1437,474,1254]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
Diagnosis. Distinguished from similar congeners by shapes of procursus (distal structures, 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FB38093D3F0CFD76" box="[1221,1318,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 526</figureCitation>
; similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FA7A093C3B23FD52" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atomarius">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FA7A093C3B23FD52" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. atomarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FEB709D93B88FD52" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[330,418,654,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uisib">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FEB709D93B88FD52" box="[330,418,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. uisib</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), bulb (processes of embolus, 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FCE909D93950FD52" box="[788,890,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 529</figureCitation>
; similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FC1B09D93E52FD52" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[998,1144,654,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atomarius">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FC1B09D93E52FD52" box="[998,1144,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. atomarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FB4709D93F38FD52" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[1210,1298,654,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uisib">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FB4709D93F38FD52" box="[1210,1298,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. uisib</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), cheliceral apophyses (with proximal humps; 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FDD709E538FCFD3E" box="[554,726,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Figs. 527, 528</figureCitation>
), shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FC2309E53E6EFD3E" box="[990,1092,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 459–474" captionStartId="75.[151,258,1476,1497]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,167,1452]" captionTargetId="figure-242@75.[151,1436,167,1452]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 459–474. Smeringopus hypocrita group, epigyna, ventral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. 459–460. S. hypocrita. 461–462. S. sederberg. 463–464. S. lotzi. 465–466. S. ubicki. 467–468. S. dehoop. 469–470. S. atomarius. 471–472. S. uisib. 473–474. S. tombua." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415770/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 473</figureCitation>
; wide plate with small round pockets; like 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FED109813B90FD1A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[300,442,726,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atomarius">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FED109813B90FD1A" box="[300,442,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. atomarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FE0D09813868FD1A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[496,578,726,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uisib">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FE0D09813868FD1A" box="[496,578,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. uisib</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and spotted leg femora (only proximally).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFD31755FF3A09AD387AFB36" blockId="86.[151,1437,474,1254]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
Male (
<typeStatus id="54E9BA86FFD31755FEED09AD3B53FCE6" box="[272,377,762,786]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total body length 6.2, carapace width 1.7. Leg 1: 43.6 (12.5 + 0.8 + 10.8 + 17.5 + 2.0), tibia 2: 8.0, tibia 3: 6.0, tibia 4: 8.8; tibia 1 L/d: 55. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FCC608493E2CFCC2" box="[827,1030,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 424–437" captionStartId="72.[151,258,1772,1793]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,329,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-143@72.[152,1437,329,1757]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 424–437. Smeringopus hypocrita group, habitus. 424–425. S. hypocrita, male, dorsal view and female, ventral view. 426–427. S. sederberg, male, dorsal and ventral views. 428–429. S. lotzi, male, dorsal and ventral views. 430–431. S. dehoop, male, dorsal view and female, ventral view. 432–433. S. atomarius, female, dorsal and ventral views. 434–435. S. uisib, female, dorsal and ventral views. 436–437. S. tombua, male, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415764/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Figs. 436 and 437</figureCitation>
. Carapace ochre-yellow with brown median and very indistinct lateral marks, clypeus with indistinct pair of dark stripes, sternum slightly darkened medially, leg femora with some brown spots proximally, femora and tibiae with indistinct subdistal rings, abdomen monochromous pale whitish. Distance PME-PME 115 µm, diameter PME 150 µm, distance PME-ALE 55 µm, distance AME-AME 60 µm, diameter AME 135 µm. Ocular area slightly elevated, secondary eyes with small ‘pseudo-lenses’; deep thoracic pit. Chelicerae with conical proximal humps and distal apophyses (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FB1408853FBAFC1E" box="[1257,1424,978,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Figs. 527, 528</figureCitation>
). Palps as in 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FEE308A13BD8FBFA" box="[286,498,1014,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 451–458" captionStartId="74.[151,257,1974,1995]" captionTargetBox="[178,1422,924,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-361@74.[178,1422,924,1951]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 451–458. Smeringopus hypocrita group, left male palps, prolateral and retrolateral views. 451–452. S. dehoop. 453–454. S. atomarius. 455–456. S. uisib. 457–458. S. tombua." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415768/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Figs. 457 and 458</figureCitation>
, coxa with distinct retrolateral apophysis, trochanter barely modified, femur with retrolateral furrow with distinct proximal rim, procursus with distinctive distal processes in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FAC80F4D3FBDFBC6" box="[1333,1431,1050,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 526</figureCitation>
; retrolateral view as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FE6B0F693BC3FBA2" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[406,489,1086,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uisib">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FE6B0F693BC3FBA2" box="[406,489,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. uisib</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FDE30F6938AAFBA2" box="[542,640,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 505–513" captionStartId="83.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[189,1404,515,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-183@83.[183,1407,507,1932]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="FIGURES 505–513. Smeringopus atomarius (505–508) and S. uisib (509–513). 505, 510. Left procursi, dorsal views. 506–507, 511–512. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal views. 508, 513. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. 509. Left cymbium and procursus, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415780/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 509</figureCitation>
), bulb with complex embolus, distinctive in prolateral view (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FAC80F693FB2FBA2" box="[1333,1432,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 526–529" captionStartId="86.[151,258,1942,1963]" captionTargetBox="[196,1403,1306,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-456@86.[187,1411,1291,1924]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 526–529. Smeringopus tombua. 526. Left procursus, dorsal view. 527–528. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 529. Left embolus, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415784/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 529</figureCitation>
; dorsal view as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFD31755FE990F343B93FB8F" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[356,441,1123,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uisib">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFD31755FE990F343B93FB8F" box="[356,441,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">S. uisib</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFD31755FE0D0F35387EFB8E" box="[496,596,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 505–513" captionStartId="83.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[189,1404,515,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-183@83.[183,1407,507,1932]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="FIGURES 505–513. Smeringopus atomarius (505–508) and S. uisib (509–513). 505, 510. Left procursi, dorsal views. 506–507, 511–512. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal views. 508, 513. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. 509. Left cymbium and procursus, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415780/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 512</figureCitation>
). Legs without spines, few vertical hairs, with curved hairs on tibiae and metatarsi 1 and 2; retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia 1 at 2.5%; prolateral trichobothrium present on tibia 1. Gonopore with two epiandrous spigots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFD31755FF3A0F993907FB12" blockId="86.[151,1437,474,1254]" box="[199,813,1230,1254]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
